The paper deals with generating images from a given layout, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) to encode object categories, which is a sub-topic of computational linguistics (CL). Finally, the paper uses bounding boxes to represent object locations, which is a sub-topic of computer graphics (GR).
